    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @eulerbeat \r\n\r\nThis is part of [EIP-1271](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1271). \r\n\r\nThe short answer is yes\r\n\r\nWe are asking `signer` if he recognizes the signature. If so, then we can act on its behalf. If the signer doesn't implement EIP-1271 properly, then its assets are at risks (but only its). Basically, we consider \"signer\" is the only one that decides how its identity is being used, and that is qualified to check its own signature (or signature it wants to accept as its own).",
